				 Held for theft of patients jewellery
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Ratna Naskar, 32, was arrested on Sunday on charges of stealing jewellery from the patients of a nursing home in Tiljala.																								Ratna worked in the nursing home as a nurse-cum-ayah. She was picked up from her south Calcutta residence by a team from the detective department. Some of the stolen items were recovered from her house.																								The police said Ratna joined the nursing home a month ago. She used to steal the ornaments either when the patients changed or while they were asleep.																								The nursing home authorities approached the police following a rise in the number of thefts.
